ring%20a%20very%20different%20mantra%20for%20handling%20anxiety%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20said%20that%20while%20he%20does%20feel%20anxious%2C%20he%20is%20in%20a%20position%20where%20he%20has%20to%20control%20his%20emotions%20and%20one%20way%20of%20doing%20that%20is%20to%20counter%20restlessness%20by%20going%20along%20with%20one's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20podcast%20with%20Nikhil%20Kamath%2C%20the%20co-founder%20of%20Zerodha%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20cited%20examples%20of%20how%20he%20dealt%20with%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20elections%20-%20which%20he%20called%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20of%20his%20life%20-%20blasts%20in%20the%20state%20and%20the%20Godhra%20train%20burning%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%2C%20to%20manage%20these%20things%2C%20everyone%20has%20his%20own%20ability%20and%20individual%20style...%20I%20hold%20such%20a%20position%20that%20I%20have%20to%20control%20my%20emotions%20--%20the%20natural%20tendency%20that%20human%20beings%20have%2C%20I%20will%20have%20to%20stay%20detached%20from%20all%20of%20that.%20I%20will%20have%20to%20rise%20above%20all%20that.%20For%20example%2C%20in%202002%2C%20there%20were%20elections%20in%20Gujarat.%20It%20was%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20of%20my%20life...%20I%20never%20watched%20TV%20and%20didn't%20check%20the%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20PM%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%2011%3A00%20am%20or%20noon%2C%20I%20heard%20the%20beat%20of%20drums%20outside%20the%20chief%20minister's%20bungalow.%20I%20had%20told%20everyone%20not%20to%20inform%20me%20till%2012%20pm.%20Then%20our%20operator%20sent%20me%20a%20letter%20saying%20I%20was%20leading%20with%20a%20two-thirds%20majority.%20So%2C%20I%20don't%20believe%20that%20nothing%20affected%20me%20that%20day%2C%20but%20I%20had%20a%20thought%20to%20overpower%20that%20feeling.%20You%20can%20say%20that%20there%20was%20restlessness%20and%20anxiety%20inside%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20bomb%20blasts%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20who%20was%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20state%20at%20the%20time%2C%20said%20he%20visited%20hospitals%20and%20the%20police%20control%20room%20despite%20his%20security%20team%20asking%20him%20not%20to.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20bombings%20in%20five%20places.%20You%20can%20imagine%20my%20situation%2C%20being%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20of%20the%20state.%20So%2C%20I%20said%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20to%20the%20police%20control%20room.%20But%20my%20security%20team%20refused.%20They%20said%2C%20'Sir%2C%20it%20will%20be%20unsafe%20for%20you%20to%20go'.%20I%20said%2C%20'Whatever%20happens%20will%20happen%2C%20I%20will%20go'.%20They%20were%20very%20worried.%20Finally%2C%20I%20sat%20in%20the%20car.%20I%20said%20that%20I%20would%20go%20to%20the%20hospital%20first.%20They%20said%20that%20there%20were%20bombings%20in%20the%20hospitals%20too.%20I%20said%20again%2C%20'Whatever%20happens%2C%20I%20will%20go'.%20You%20can%20say%20that%20there%20was%20restlessness%20and%20anxiety%20inside%20me.%20But%20my%20approach%20was%20that%20I%20would%20go%20along%20with%20my%20mission.%20Maybe%20I%20experience%20that%20in%20a%20different%20way.%20I%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20responsibility%20towards%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20the%20Godhra%20train%20burning%2C%20PM%20Modi%20said%20he%20became%20an%20MLA%20for%20the%20first%20time%20on%20February%2024%2C%202002.%20He%20went%20to%20the%20Assembly%20for%20the%20first%20time%20three%20days%20later%2C%20on%20February%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20been%20an%20MLA%20for%20only%20three%20days.%20And%2C%20suddenly%2C%20I%20came%20to%20know%20about%20that%20big%20incident%20in%20Godhra.%20There%20was%20a%20fire%20on%20the%20train.%20I%20came%20to%20know%2C%20gradually%2C%20that%20people%20were%20dead.%20I%20was%20obviously%20very%20restless%2C%20I%20was%20worried.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%