cretary%2C%20given%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20upcoming%20presidency%20of%20Trump%2C%20and%20several%20multilateral%20meetings.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20India%20has%20been%20slowly%20increasing%20its%20interaction%20with%20the%20Taliban%2C%20quietly%20acknowledging%20their%20representatives%20in%20the%20embassy%2C%20and%2C%20recently%2C%20even%20sending%20JP%20Singh%20from%20the%20Ministry%20to%20make%20the%20first%20formal%20outreach%20in%20a%20long%20time.%20Not%20that%20Indian%20assistance%20for%20the%20beleaguered%20Afghan%20people%20ever%20stopped%2C%20as%20most%20people%20tend%20to%20believe.%20As%20the%20Taliban%20took%20over%2C%20Delhi%20allocated%20Rs%20200%20crore%20for%20aid%20and%20was%20the%20first%20responder%20in%20the%20massive%20earthquake%20that%20took%20place%20that%20year%2C%20with%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20flying%20in%20tons%20of%20relief%20aid%2C%20including%20one%20shipment%20through%20Pakistan.%20But%20difficulties%20created%20by%20Islamabad%E2%80%94the%20insistence%20that%20Pakistani%20trucks%20be%20used%2C%20something%20presented%20as%20Pakistan's%20%E2%80%98generosity'%20then%E2%80%94led%20to%20a%20revival%20of%20the%20Chabahar%20route%20in%202023%20to%20deliver%20about%2020%2C000%20tons%20of%20wheat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi's%20logic%20was%20simple.%20It%20had%20always%20been%20a%20friend%20to%20the%20Afghan%20people%20and%20wasn't%20going%20to%20desert%20them%2C%20Taliban%20or%20no%20Taliban.%20In%20fact%2C%20Taliban%20leaders%20even%20met%20with%20Indian%20officials%20regarding%20aid%20and%20requested%20that%20small%20projects%20be%20restarted%2C%20among%20a%20bevy%20of%20other%20projects%20that%20India%20had%20been%20backing.%20There%20was%20a%20time%20when%20India%20was%20providing%20Afghanistan%20extensive%20assistance%E2%80%94some%20400%20projects%20across%20Afghanistan's%2034%20provinces%2C%20including%20large%20infrastructure%20projects%20like%20the%20Salma%20dam%2C%20three%20Airbus%20aircraft%20for%20Ariana%20airways%2C%20roads%2C%20telecommunication%2C%20schools%2C%20banking%20expertise%2C%20and%20even%20%2420%2C000%20for%20restoration%20of%20the%20shrine%20of%20Imam%20Hazrat%20Ali.%20Defence%20aid%20included%20supply%20of%20vehicles%20for%20the%20army%20and%20over%201%2C000%20training%20slots%20with%20the%20Indian%20army%2C%20the%20largest%20for%20any%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaturally%2C%20Pakistan%20was%20deeply%20insecure.%20The%20Islamic%20State%20Khorasan%20suddenly%20turned%20anti-India.%20It%20attacked%20a%20gurdwara%20that%20killed%20dozens%20and%20claimed%20the%20attacks%20in%20Coimbatore%20and%20Mangalore%20in%202022.%20Al%20Qaeda%20chief%20Al%20Zawahari%2C%20too%2C%20was%20seen%20praising%20a%20Karnataka%20girl%20for%20defending%20the%20hijab.%20But%20then%2C%20the%20IS-K%20always%20had%20a%20Pakistan%20hand.%20Remember%20the%20arrest%20of%20Aslam%20Farooqi%20earlier%2C%20along%20with%20a%20Pakistan-trained%20Bangladeshi%2C%20and%20another%20from%20Islamabad%3F%20Farooqi%20had%20earlier%20been%20part%20of%20the%20fight%20in%20Kashmir.%20When%20Islamabad%20pressed%20for%20his%20extradition%2C%20Kabul%20refused.%20In%20sum%2C%20the%20long%20tail%20of%20accountability%20indicates%20a%20strong%20Pakistani%20link%20with%20at%20least%20one%20part%20of%20IS-K.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Pakistani%20Reaction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20us%20back%20to%20the%20Foreign%20Secretary's%20visit.%20Islamabad%20is%20likely%20to%20see%20the%20trip%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20the%20recent%20crisis%20in%20Afghanistan-Pakistan%20relations.%20The%20wording%20of%20Delhi's%20protest%20note%20is%20also%20interesting%2C%20since%20it%20echoes%20almost%20exactly%20what%20the%20Taliban%20have%20been%20saying%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20an%20old%20practice%20of%20Pakistan%20to%20blame%20its%20neighbours%20for%20its%20own%20internal%20failures%E2%80%9D.%20It%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20also%20noted%20the%20response%20of%20an%20Afghan%20spokesperson%20in%20this%20regard%E2%80%9D.%20The%20response%20in%20question%2C%20from%20the%20Defence%20Ministry%2C%20was%20unequivocal%20in%20noting%20that%20the%20blatant%20attack%20on%20Afghan%20sovereignty%20would%20not%20be%20left%20unanswered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20sounds%20dangerous.%20Afghanistan%20doesn't%20have%20much%20of%20an%20army%2C%20but%20it%20does%20have%20the%20capability%20to%20launch%20exactly%20what%20Pakistan%20trained%20it%20in%2C%20for%20decades%3A%20low-intensity%2C%20high-stakes%2C%20conflict.%20Pakistan%20witnessed%20a%2040%25%20rise%20in%20terrorism%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Pakistan%20Institute%20for%20Conflict%20and%20Security%20Studies.%20That's%20not%20all.%20There's%20been%20a%2021%25%20rise%20in%20casualties%2C%20indicating%20more%20capability%20for%20violence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20second%20%E2%80%9Cdecisive%E2%80%9D%20shift.%20The%20Pakistan%20army%20is%20killing%20more%20(51%25)%20and%20arresting%20less.%20That%20can't%20be%20pleasant%20for%20the%20locals.%20Which%20is%20also%20how%20the%20Pashtun%20Tahafuz%20Movement%20(PTM)%20emerged.%20An%20entirely%20peaceful%20movement%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20charismatic%20Manzoor%20Pashteen%2C%20it%20has%20been%20demanding%20an%20end%20to%20the%20depredations%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20army%2C%20including%20bombing%20houses%20and%20blowing%20off%20roofs%2C%20and%20humiliating%20checks%20and%20search%20operations.%20It%20held%20a%20massive%20jirga%20calling%20for%20an%20open%20border%20and%20stated%20its%20determination%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20TTP%20in%20its%20own%20way.%20Rawalpindi%20reacted%20by%20banning%20it%20and%20arresting%20its%20leaders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20down%20the%20border%2C%20a%20full-blown%20conflict%20in%20Kurram%2C%20once%20the%20main%20infiltration%20point%20to%20Kabul%2C%20has%20created%20another%20set%20of%20issues.%20Lakki%20Marwat%20in%20the%20Bannu%20division%20has%20seen%20a%20police%20uprising%20demanding%20that%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20remove%20themselves%20and%20leave%20operations%20to%20locals.%20That's%20the%20key.%20The%20TTP%20is%20almost%20entirely%20from%20tribal%20areas%20and%20was%20driven%20out%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20in%20one%20of%20its%20innumerable%20operations%2C%20only%20to%20then%20fight%20alongside%20the%20Taliban.%20The%20present%20TTP%20is%20an%20amalgam%20of%20some%20seven%20to%20eight%20disparate%20groups%20that%20straddle%20the%20border.%20So%2C%20the%20Taliban's%20plea%E2%80%94backed%20by%20India%E2%80%94that%20the%20terrorism%20issue%20is%20wholly%20a%20Pakistani%20problem%2C%20is%20legitimate%2C%20not%20just%20regarding%20the%20TTP%20but%20also%20about%20the%20long-festering%20Baloch%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Dangerous%20Clash%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Christmas%20air%20attacks%2C%20the%20TTP%20reacted%20dangerously.%20First%2C%20it%20issued%20a%20warning%20that%20it%20would%20not%20allow%20any%20transactions%20with%20Pakistan-army%20owned%20entities%20or%20fronts%2C%20including%20Fauji%20Cement%20Company%20Ltd.%2C%20Askari%20Bank%20Ltd.%2C%20Fauji%20Fertilizer%20Company%20Ltd.%2C%20Fauji%20Foods%20Ltd.%2C%20Askari%20Cement%20Ltd.%2C%20Askari%20Fuels%2C%20National%20Logistic%20Cell%2C%20Frontier%20Works%20Organization%2C%20Pakistan%20Ordnance%20Factory%2C%20Fauji%20Foundation%20and%20the%20Defence%20Housing%20Authority%2C%20among%20others.%20All%20of%20these%20entities%20contribute%2C%20quietly%2C%20to%20the%20vast%20wealth%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20army.%20The%20TTP%20has%20given%20shopkeepers%20two%20months%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20their%20stocks.%20A%20video%20circulating%20online%20also%20seems%20to%20show%20that%20the%20TTP%20has%20kidnapped%20some%2016%20persons%20working%20at%20the%20Qabul%20Khel%20mining%20site%20in%20Lakki%20Marwat.%20While%20some%20have%20reportedly%20been%20rescued%2C%20it's%20still%20a%20bad%20sign.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20some%20800%20Afghans%20have%20been%20picked%20up%20in%20Islamabad.%20The%20army%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20know%20where%20to%20stop%2C%20even%20after%20it%20arbitrarily%20pushed%20out%20hundreds%20of%20Afghans%20from%20its%20country.%20The%20strife%20is%20unlikely%20to%20end%20well.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%20seems%20set%20on%20a%20stabilisation%20route.%20Delhi%20in%20its%20statement%20has%20committed%20aid%20to%20refugees%20and%20other%20areas.%20India%20doesn't%20need%20to%20supply%20weapons%2C%20given%20that%20the%20Afghans%20have%20plenty%20of%20their%20own%2C%20%E2%80%98gifted'%20by%20a%20departing%20US%20military.%20What%20Muttaqi%20has%20been%20really%20stressing%20instead%20is%20economic%20development%2C%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20a%20regional%20thrust%20to%20stop%20Islamic%20state%20recruitment.%20That%20is%20going%20to%20sit%20well%20with%20Russia%2C%20which%20has%20called%20for%20a%20dialling%20down%20of%20tensions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20China%2C%20which%20has%20an%20abiding%20fear%20of%20religious%20extremism.%20Oddly%2C%20all%20three%20have%20similar%20objectives%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20which%20centre%20around%20stability%20for%20the%20country.%20While%20India%20recently%20invited%20Afghan%20businessmen%20to%20use%20the%20Chabahar%20port%20as%20a%20way%20to%20bypass%20Pakistani%20tantrums%2C%20China%20is%20said%20to%20be%20developing%20a%20route%20through%20the%20Wakhan%20corridor%2C%20with%20possibly%20the%20same%20objective.%20Also%2C%20both%20Russia%20and%20China%20can%20use%20the%20Central%20Asian%20route%20to%20move%20Afghan%20trade.%20Amid%20all%20this%2C%20Islamabad%20has%20seemingly%20lost%20the%20plot.%20Everyone%20is%20moving%20on%2C%20towards%20connectivity%20and%20trade%2C%20areas%20where%20Islamabad%20could%20excel%20if%20it%20wanted%20to.%20But%20it%20does%20not.%20Instead%2C%20it%20is%20intent%20on%20blaming%20everyone%20and%20anyone%20for%20a%20dangerously%20spiralling%20conflict%20that%20could%20see%20tribal%20areas%20parting%20ways%20with%20an%20ungenerous%20and%20suspicious%20Punjabi%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20bottom%20line%20that%20Pakistani%20leaders%20need%20to%20recognise.%20They%20can%20either%20have%20their%20country%20at%20peace%20or%20a%20group%20of%20insurgents%20at%20war.%20They%20can't%20have%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Tara%20Kartha%20is%20a%20former%20Director%2C%20National%20Security%20Council%20Secretariat.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736505480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fdaqig02c_vikram-misri-afghan-foreign-minister-mawlawi-amir-khan-muttaqi_625x300_08_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-an-india-taliban-softening-irks-pakistan-so-7442768%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Everyone%20is%20moving%20on%20with%20respect%20to%20Afghanistan%2C%20towards%20connectivity%20and%20trade%2C%20areas%20where%20Islamabad%20could%20excel%20if%20it%20wanted%20to.%20But%20it%20does%20not.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-an-india-taliban-softening-irks-pakistan-so-7442768%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20retirement%20savings%20are%20on%20track.%20Here's%20why%20I%20still%20might%20never%20retire.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225973%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20working%20from%20home%20at%20desk%20with%20laptop%20with%20a%20puppy%20on%20his%20lap.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677fe18ff83fcec7e5b531df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(not%20pictured)%20loves%20his%20job%2C%20and%20says%20he%20may%20never%20retire.%3Cp%3EJessie%20Casson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI've%20been%20saving%20for%20retirement%20for%20most%20of%20my%20career%20and%20should