0on%20the%20perfect%20storm%20that%20created%20equity-like%20risk%20returns%20in%20the%20credit%20space.%20Over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20the%20rising%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-fixed-income-investing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisk-free%3C%2Fa%3E%20rate%20pushed%20up%20the%20threshold%20for%20taking%20on%20more%20risk.%20Investors%20began%20looking%20outside%20the%20realms%20of%20tight%20spreads.%20Meanwhile%2C%20supply%20rose%20to%20meet%20the%20growing%20demand%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapollo-global-management-investor-day-presentation-one-trillion-private-lending-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einstitutional%20players%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hedge%20funds%2C%20and%20private%20equity%20could%20raise%20capital%20to%20chase%20those%20higher%20yields.%20All%20the%20while%2C%20banks%20were%20scaling%20back%20on%20lending%20to%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20private%20credit%2C%20you%20cut%20that%20J%20curve%20significantly%20because%20you%20don't%20need%20time%20for%20the%20investment%2C%20like%20on%20the%20private%20equity%20side%2C%20to%20mature%20and%20show%20some%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Karger%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20private%20credit%2C%20the%20borrowers%20typically%20pay%20out%20of%20the%20gate.%20There's%20a%20current%20cash%20component%20that%20can%20run%20anywhere%20from%20high%20single-digits%2C%20eight%2C%20nine%2C%2010%25%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%2020%25%20type%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20borrowers%2C%20private%20credit%20managers%20have%20been%20able%20to%20move%20faster%20and%20be%20more%20flexible%20in%20lending%20standards%20than%20traditional%20banks.%20So%20the%20deals%20can%20look%20attractive%20for%20both%20sides%2C%20Karger%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcia%20Nelson%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20Freedom%20Family%20Office%2C%20who%20frequents%20her%20industry's%20conferences%20and%20hosts%20a%20few%20herself%2C%20says%20the%20private%20credit%20space%20has%20been%20the%20newest%20conversation%20piece%20over%20the%20last%20six%20months.%20She's%20seeing%20a%20particular%20interest%20in%20lending%20through%20the%20US%20Small%20Business%20Administration%20(SBA)%2C%20something%20she%20attributes%20to%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20a%20slowing%20private%20equity%20market%20faced%20with%20fewer%20IPOs%20and%20prolonged%20returns%20on%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20I'm%20hearing%20from%20families%20is%20that%20they%20are%20moving%20some%20of%20their%20allocations%20out%20of%20private%20equity%20and%20out%20of%20direct%20deals%20into%20direct%20private%20credit%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20part%20of%20it%20is%20they're%20just%20seeing%20that%20there's%20really%20great%20investment%20opportunities%2C%20and%20the%20returns%20are%20really%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-ultra-high-net-worth-investors-are-buying-family-office-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFamily%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E'%20conservative%20approach%20and%20wealth%20preservation%20mandate%20also%20means%20they're%20more%20concerned%20with%20high%20equity%20valuations.%20Private%20credit%20provides%20an%20additional%20diversifier%20with%20uncorrelated%20investments%20that%20can%20be%20customized.%20Some%20managers%20are%20even%20lending%20to%20esoteric%20borrowers%20such%20as%20the%20defense%20sector%20or%20music%20rights%20deals%2C%20Karger%20noted.%20They%20can%20opt%20for%20investment%20durations%20as%20short%20as%20six%20months%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%2012%20years%2C%20depending%20on%20whether%20it's%20direct%20lending%20or%20done%20through%20a%20fund%20manager%20who%20requires%20a%20lock-up%20period%20to%20recycle%20the%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20buyer%20beware.%20The%20risk%20is%20in%20the%20details%2C%20and%20in%20a%20sector%20that%20isn't%20pegged%20to%20fixed%20standards%20like%20credit%20ratings%2C%20they%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20snuff%20out.%20The%20team%20leading%20the%20fund%20matters.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20those%20tasked%20with%20the%20underwriting%20and%20due%20diligence%20should%20have%20a%20shared%20background%20in%20the%20industries%20of%20the%20borrowers%20they're%20vetting%2C%20Karger%20noted.%20The%20lending%20should%20be%20limited%20to%20sectors%20where%20there%20are%20credit%20needs.%20The%20fund%20should%20also%20have%20some%20competitive%20edge%2C%20such%20as%20a%20proprietary%20database%20or%20system%20they%20use%20to%20find%20and%20vet%20deals.%20And%20finally%2C%20the%20management%20fees%20must%20be%20more%20incentivized%20than%20fixed%2C%20Karger%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENayan%20Lapsiwala%2C%20director%20of%20wealth%20management%20at%20Aspiriant%2C%20emphasized%20that%20many%20borrowers%20tend%20to%20be%20higher%20risk%2C%20highly%20leveraged%2C%20and%20tied%20to%20the%20floating%20rate%2C%20making%20them%20very%20sensitive%20to%20shocks%2C%20especially%20if%20rates%20spike%20amid%20an%20economic%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeverage%20can%20be%20on%20both%20sides%20and%20so%20you%20have%20to%20take%20that%20into%20account%2C%26quot%3B%20Lapsiwala%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20investor%20might%20also%20be%20borrowing%20money%20to%20invest%20into%20this%2C%20and%20the%20company%20that%20they%20are%20investing%20in%20is%20also%20highly%20levered.%20So%20there%20can%20be%20hidden%20leverage%20that%20people%20don't%20pay%20attention%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20that%20the%20hurdle%20rate%2C%20which%20is%20the%20minimum%20acceptable%20return%20before%20fees%2C%20shouldn't%20be%20at%20something%20as%20low%20as%205%25%20to%206%25%20or%20near%20the%20risk-free%20rate%2C%20said%20Rajesh%20Bansal%2C%20co-founder%20of%20private%20credit%20fund%20Quiq%20Capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20if%20a%20manager%20is%20willing%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20equity%20of%20a%20certain%20company%2C%20then%20they're%20definitely%20willing%20to%20invest%20in%20its%20debt%20because%20debt%20is%20ahead%20of%20equity%20holders%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20for%20bankruptcy%20or%20liquidation%2C%20Lapsiwala%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20investors%20must%20also%20consider%20the%20tax%20burden%2C%20which%20could%20be%20less%20favorable.%20For%20non-taxable%20investors%2C%20such%20as%20foundations%20and%20endowments%2C%20it's%20a%20very%20suitable%20asset%20class.%20But%20for%20US-taxable%20investors%2C%20the%20returns%20have%20to%20be%20juicier%20to%20make%20it%20worthwhile%2C%20more%20like%20north%20of%2015%25%20to%2020%25%2C%20Karger%20said.%20That's%20because%20you'll%20get%20a%20tax%20bill%20on%20the%20gross%20returns%20and%20take%20a%20hit%20on%20high%20management%20fees%20that%20aren't%20deductible.%20Some%20of%20those%20fees%20are%20charged%20on%20the%20total%20leverage.%20This%20means%20an%20investor%20could%20pay%20tax%20on%20a%2020%25%20return%20while%20only%20receiving%2012%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-why-the-ultra-wealthy-are-piling-into-private-credit-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736505001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677d60884fdf00939ed692dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-why-the-ultra-wealthy-are-piling-into-private-credit-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20expanding%20asset%20class%20is%20offering%20customizable%20equity-like%20risk%20returns.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A31%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-why-the-ultra-wealthy-are-piling-into-private-credit-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Shark%20Tank'%20star%20Kevin%20O'Leary%20is%20part%2