ter%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20like%20many%20others%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20reconnecting%20with%20old%20interests.%20As%20people%20across%20the%20world%20took%20up%20hobbies%20like%20gardening%20and%20pottery%2C%20Chokhone%20returned%20to%20her%20childhood%20passion%3A%20floriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20started%20growing%20flowers%20in%20a%20small%20patch%20of%20land%20near%20my%20house%2C%20and%20slowly%2C%20people%20started%20taking%20interest%20and%20placing%20small%20orders%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20It%20was%20in%20these%20early%20days%20that%20Dianthe%20began%20to%20take%20shape.%20%E2%80%9CSince%20there%20was%20a%20little%20demand%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20how%20to%20connect%20with%20sellers%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20why%20not%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20business%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229253875046%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhen%20are%20you%20going%20back%20to%20the%20city%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20transition%20from%20hobbyist%20to%20entrepreneur%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20immediate.%20Chokhone%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20especially%20her%20parents%2C%20were%20sceptical%20at%20first.%20After%20all%2C%20she%20had%20gone%20through%20the%20conventional%20educational%20route%2C%20getting%20a%20degree%20in%20Biotechnology%20from%20Guwahati%2C%20and%20interning%20at%20a%20pharmaceutical%20company%20in%20Bengaluru.%20In%20Mao%2C%20where%20job%20security%20and%20a%20stable%20career%20were%20prioritised%2C%20her%20decision%20to%20pursue%20floriculture%20was%20met%20with%20concern.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20told%20my%20parents%20about%20my%20plan%20to%20work%20with%20flowers%2C%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20very%20convinced.%20Even